obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (70348)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00111_189205_1666334510811&sectionId=70348&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00111_189205_1666334510811
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Bengal Military Police`
  line `Act, 1892.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of the territories subject to the Lieutenant-Governor of Bengal: and`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such day as the Local Government may, by notification in the Calcutta`
  line `Gazette, appoint in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (70349)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00111_189205_1666334510811&sectionId=70349&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00111_189205_1666334510811
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is something repugnant in the subject or context,—`
  line
  line `(1) “Military Police-officer” means a person appointed to the Bengal Police Force under section 7 of`
  line `Act V of 1861, who has signed the statement in the schedule to this act, in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of this Act:`
  line
  line `(2) “active service” means service against hostile tribes or other persons in the filed:`
  line
  line `(3) “District Magistrate” includes a Deputy Commissioner, an Assistant Commissioner in charge of a`
  line `sub-division, and the Superintendent of the South Lushai Hill:`
  line
  line `(4) “Commandant” means a person appointed by the Local Government to be a Commandant of`
  line `Military Police and includes a District Superintendent of Police and an Assistant District Superintendent of`
  line `Police in charge of the civil police of a district or of a sub-division:`
  line
  line `(5) “Second-in-Command” means a person appointed by the Local Government to be a Second-inCommand of Military Police, and includes an Assistant District Superintendent of Police not in charge of`
  line `the civil police of a district or of a sub-division: and`
  line
  line `(6) the expression “reason to believe,” “criminal force,” “assault,” “fraudulently” and “voluntarily`
  line `causing hurt” have the meaning assigned to them respectively in the Indian Penal Code (XV of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (70350)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Enrolment and discharge of Military Police-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00111_189205_1666334510811&sectionId=70350&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00111_189205_1666334510811
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Before an officer appointed to the`
  line `Bengal Police Force under section 7 of Act V of 1861 is appointed to be a Military Police-officer, the`
  line `statement in the schedule shall be read and if necessary explained to him in the presence of a Magistrate,`
  line `Commandant or Second-in-Command, and shall be signed by him in acknowledgment of its having been`
  line `so read to him.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding any notice given under section 9 of Act V of 1861, a Military Police-officer shall`
  line `not be entitled to be discharged from the Bengal Police Force except in accordance with the terms of the`
  line `statement which he has signed under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (70351)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Classes and grades of Military Police-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00111_189205_1666334510811&sectionId=70351&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00111_189205_1666334510811
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) There may be all or any of the following`
  line `classes of Military Police-officers, which shall take rank in the order mentioned, namely: —`
  line
  line `(i) subadars-major,`
  line
  line `(ii) subadars,`
  line
  line `(iii) jamadars,`
  line
  line `(iv) havildars-major,`
  line
  line `(v) havildars,`
  line
  line `(iv) naiks,`
  line
  line `(vii) buglers, and`
  line
  line `(viii) sepoys,`
  line
  line `and such grades in each class as the Local Government may direct.`
  line
  line `(2) The expression “superior officer” in this Act means in relation to any Police-officer—`
  line
  line `(a) any officer of a higher class than or of a higher grade in the same class as himself, and`
  line
  line `(b) any Second-in-Command, Commandant or District Magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (70352)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `More heinous offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00111_189205_1666334510811&sectionId=70352&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00111_189205_1666334510811
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `A Military Police-officer who`
  line
  line `(a) begins, excites, causes or joins in any mutiny or sedition or, being present at any mutiny or`
  line `sedition, does not use his utmost endeavors to suppress it, or, knowing or having reason to believe in`
  line `the existence of any mutiny, or of any intention to mutiny, does not without delay give information`
  line `thereof to his commanding or other superior officer; or`
  line
  line `(b) uses, or attempts to use, criminal force to or commits an assault on, his superior officer, whether`
  line `on or off duty; or`
  line
  line `(c) shamefully abandons or delivers up any garrison, fortress, post or guard which is committed to`
  line `his charge or which it is his duty to defend; or`
  line
  line `(d) directly or indirectly holds correspondence with, or assists or relieves, any person in arms`
  line `against the State, or omits to discover immediately to his commanding or other superior officer any`
  line `such correspondence coming to his knowledge: or`
  line
  line `who, while on active service,-`
  line
  line `(e) disobeys the lawful command of his superior officer; or`
  line
  line `(f) deserts the service; or`
  line
  line `(g) being a sentry, sleeps upon his post, or quits it without being regularly relieved or without`
  line `leave; or`
  line
  line `(h) without authority leaves his commanding officer, or his post or party, to go in search of plunder;`
  line or
  line
  line `(i) quits his guard, picquet, party or patrol without being regularly relieved or without leave; or`
  line
  line `(j) uses criminal force to, or commits an assault on, any person bringing provisions or other`
  line `necessaries to camp or quarters, or forces safeguard, or without authority breaks into any house or any`
  line `other place for plunder, or plunders, destroys or damages any property of any kind; or`
  line
  line `(k) intentionally causes or spreads a false alarm in action, camp, garrison or quarters,`
  line
  line `shall be punished with transportation for life or for a term of not less than seven years, or with imprisonment`
  line `for a term much may extend to fourteen years, or with fine which may extend to three months' pay, or with`
  line `fine to that extent in addition to such sentence of transportation or imprisonment, as the case may be, as`
  line `may be passed upon him under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (70353)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Less heinous offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00111_189205_1666334510811&sectionId=70353&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00111_189205_1666334510811
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `A Military Police-officer who`
  line
  line `(a) is in a state of, intoxication when on or for any duty or on parade or on the line of march; or`
  line
  line `(b) strikes or attempts to force any sentry; or,`
  line
  line `(c) being in command of a guard, picquet or patrol, refuses to receive any prisoner duly committed`
  line `to his charge, or without proper authority releases any prisoner, or negligently suffers any prisoner to`
  line `escape; or,`
  line
  line `(d) being under arrest or in confinement, leaves his arrest or confinement before he is set at liberty`
  line `by proper authority; or`
  line
  line `(e) is grossly insubordinate or insolent to his superior officer in the execution of his office; or`
  line
  line `(f) refuses to superintend or assist in the making of any field-work or other work of any description`
  line `ordered to be made either in quarters or in the field; or`
  line
  line `(g) strikes or otherwise ill-uses any Military Police-officer subordinate to him in rank or position;`
  line or
  line
  line `(h) being in command at any post or on the march, and receiving a complaint that any one under`
  line `his command has beaten or otherwise maltreated or oppressed any person, or has committed any riot`
  line `or trespass, fails, on proof of the truth of the complaint, to have due reparation made as far as possible`
  line `to the injured person and to report the case to the proper authority; or`
  line
  line `(i) designedly or through neglect injures or loses, or fraudulently disposes of, his arms, clothes,`
  line `tools, equipments, ammunition, accoutrements or Military Police necessaries, or any such articles`
  line `entrusted to him or belonging to any other person; or`
  line
  line `(j) malingers, or feigns or produces disease or infirmity in himself, or intentionally delays his cure,`
  line `or aggravates his disease or infirmity; or`
  line
  line `(k) with intent to render himself or any other person unfit for service, voluntarily causes hurt to`
  line `himself or any other person; or`
  line `who, while not on active service,-`
  line
  line `(l) disobeys the lawful command of his superior officer; or`
  line
  line `(m) plunders, destroys or damages any property of any kind; or`
  line
  line `(n) being a sentry, sleeps upon his post or quits it without being regularly relieved or without`
  line `leave; or`
  line
  line `(o) deserts the service;`
  line
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to three months' pay, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (70354)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Minor punishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00111_189205_1666334510811&sectionId=70354&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00111_189205_1666334510811
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) A District Magistrate, Commandant or Second-in-Command, or an`
  line `officer not being below the rank of subadar commanding a separate detachment or an outpost or in`
  line `temporary command at the headquarters of a district during the absence of the District Magistrate,`
  line `Commandant and Second-in-Command, may, without a formal trial, award to any Military Police-officer`
  line `who is subject to his authority any of the following punishments for the commission of any petty offence`
  line `against discipline which is not otherwise provided for in this Act, or which is not of a sufficiently serious`
  line `nature to call for a prosecution before a Criminal Court, that is to say—`
  line
  line `(a) imprisonment to the extent of seven days in the quarter-guard or such other place as may be`
  line `considered suitable, with forfeiture of all pay and allowances during its continuance;`
  line
  line `(b) punishment drill, extra guard, fatigue, or other duty, not exceeding thirty days in duration, with`
  line `or without confinement to quarters.`
  line
  line `(2) Any one of these punishments may be awarded separately or in combination with any one or more`
  line `of the others.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (70355)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Place of imprisonment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00111_189205_1666334510811&sectionId=70355&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00111_189205_1666334510811
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `A person sentenced under this Act to imprisonment for a period not`
  line `exceeding three months shall, when he is also dismissed from the Bengal Police Force, be imprisoned in`
  line `the nearest or such other jail as the Local Government may, by general or special order, direct; but, when`
  line `he is not also dismissed from that force, he may, if the convicting officer or District Magistrate so directs,`
  line `be confined in the quarter-guard or such other place as the convicting officer or District Magistrate may`
  line `consider suitable.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (70356)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Saving of prosecutions under other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00111_189205_1666334510811&sectionId=70356&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00111_189205_1666334510811
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing in this Act shall prevent any person from`
  line `being prosecuted under Act V of 1861, or under any order or rule made under that Act or under any other`
  line `enactment for the time being in force for any act or omission punishable hereunder, or from being liable if`
  line `so prosecuted to any other or higher penalty than is provided for that act or omission by this Act:`
  line
  line `(2) Provided that no person shall be punished twice for the same offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (70357)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Conferment of magisterial powers on Police-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00111_189205_1666334510811&sectionId=70357&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00111_189205_1666334510811
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in`
  line `Act V of 1861 or in any other enactment for the time being in force, the Local Government may invest any`
  line `Police-officer not below the rank of Commandant with the powers of Magistrate of any class for the`
  line `purpose of enquiring into or trying any offence committed by a Military Police-officer and punishable under`
  line `Act V of 1861 or this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (70358)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Disciplinary and other powers of Commandants and Seconds-in-Command of Military Police otherwise than in respect of Military Police.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00111_189205_1666334510811&sectionId=70358&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00111_189205_1666334510811
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Subject to such rules as the Local Government may make`
  line `in this behalf, a Commandant or Second-in Command of Military Police shall have, with respect to Policeofficers appointed to the Bengal Police Force under section 7 of Act V of 1861, who are not Military Policeofficers, the same disciplinary powers as a District Superintendent of Police has with respect to them under`
  line `that section.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (70359)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Privileges of Commandants and Seconds-in-Command of Military Police as Police-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00111_189205_1666334510811&sectionId=70359&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00111_189205_1666334510811
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `A Commandant or Second-in-Command of Military Police shall be entitled to all the privileges which a`
  line `Police-officer has under sections 42 and 43 of Act V of 1861, section 125 of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872`
  line `(I of 1872), and any other enactment for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (70360)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00111_189205_1666334510811&sectionId=70360&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00111_189205_1666334510811
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Local Government may, as regards the Military Police make such`
  line `orders and rules consistent with this Act as it thinks expedient.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
